  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Seed and Planting Material Support for Drought Affected People in Oromia and SNNP Regions</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Drought affected/vulnerable households</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Establishment of beneficiary selection committee, sensitization of the committee, awareness on  gender, establishing criteria of selection and detailed selection of target groups.

Procurement of seeds and planting materials.

Distribution of seeds and planting materials to target beneficiaries.

Provide on job training on best agricultural practices and technical support.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project has been designed by a consortium consisting of CARE, CRS, the Food and Agriculture Organization (FAO) and World Vision Ethiopia. This project is designed to support belg/sapie benefiting poor farming households through distribution of various types of seeds and planting materials that can be planted in the meher 2011- season.  Each agency based their seed plan on seed need assessment at farmer level and market assessment for selected seed availability in the market. This is a crucial step to understand farmers&#x2019; needs and agreement on the types of seed. CRS will focus its activities in five locations in  East and West Hararghe zones. The overall objective of the project is to contribute to food security in East and West Hararghe zones of Oromiya and Gamugofa zone of SNNP regions. The specific objective of the project is increased food supply for drought affected households by providing seed and planting materials for the remaining meher season.</narrative>
  </description>
